\begin_layout Standard
We can compute:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\mathrm{d}r}{\mathrm{d}g}=\frac{a}{(bg-1)^{2}}=\frac{(br+a)^{2}}{a}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\mathrm{d}^{2}r}{\mathrm{d}g^{2}}=-\frac{2ab}{(bg-1)^{3}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For inverse relation,
 we have:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
g=\frac{r}{a+br}
\]

\end_inset

and
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\mathrm{d}g}{\mathrm{d}r}=\frac{a}{(a+br)^{2}}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\mathrm{d}^{2}g}{\mathrm{d}r^{2}}=\frac{-2ab}{(a+br)^{3}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

