\begin_layout Standard
Multipole expansion:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{\left|\mathbf{r}-\mathbf{r}'\right|}=\sum_{lm}\frac{4\pi}{2l+1}\frac{r_{<}^{l}}{r_{>}^{l+1}}Y_{lm}^{*}(\hat{\mathbf{r}})Y_{lm}(\hat{\mathbf{r}}')
\]

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{<}=\mathrm{min}(r,r')$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{>}=\mathrm{max}(r,r')$
\end_inset


\end_layout

